📝 Flask Blog App

A simple Flask-based blog application where users can register, login, and manage their posts. Built with Flask, SQLite, and Bootstrap 5.

Features

✅ User Registration & Login with password hashing

✅ Create, Read, Update, Delete (CRUD) posts

✅ Only authors can edit or delete their own posts

✅ Flash messages for feedback

✅ Responsive UI with Bootstrap 5

✅ CSRF protection using Flask-WTF


Tech Stack

Backend: Python, Flask, Flask-WTF, Flask-SQLAlchemy

Database: SQLite

Frontend: HTML, Jinja2 Templates, Bootstrap 5


Installation

Clone the repository

git clone <your-repo-link>
cd flask-blog


Create a virtual environment

python -m venv venv


Activate the environment

Windows:

venv\Scripts\activate


macOS/Linux:

source venv/bin/activate


Install dependencies

pip install -r requirements.txt

Usage

Run the Flask app

python app.py


Open in your browser

http://127.0.0.1:5000/


What you can do:

Register a new account

Login with your credentials

Add new blog posts

Edit or delete your posts

Logout when finished

